##After the siege of Wuhan, someone shouted from the balcony, "opposite, open the window and have a quarrel. "

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

Today, on the 13th day of the city's closure, most of the 9 million people who remain in the city, apart from those who run for nucleic acid tests and beds, remain at home, unable to leave their homes except for shopping and taking out the trash. How did they get through the siege? The author's experience may be representative of the everyday life of some ordinary Wuhan families.

Phoenix News Client, produced by Phoenix Network Studio on Earth

Today, the weather is sunny, sunny, this is since the city of Wuhan, the Second Great Sunny Day. I sat on the balcony typing while the two children played. Outside the window, our washed sheets fluttered gently in the breeze.

Since the outbreak of the Wuhan epidemic, I have mixed feelings, from the very beginning of the insouciance to today's engraved heart, walked a long way, with a long journey to describe it is not too much.

This article is an experience for me and my family, which may represent the daily life of some other ordinary Wuhan families.

It was January 23, the 12th of the 12th month. Our family had a two-hour "escape" . You're asking me why I didn't leave early? There's no real reason. It's all hesitation. I interpret this hesitation as a feeling that does not rise to the level of consciousness, but always guides your actions.

On the evening of the 21st, I finally settled with Fatty (my husband) to go back home and pack up. The fat man looked at his phone and said the situation was getting worse. The fat man has always been in charge of the External Affairs of the family, and this is no exception. I have given him the right to decide when to leave. He has his doubts. A few days ago, he had a meeting with a co-worker who had been quarantined (because of an infection in his family) . Although the co-worker turned out not to be infected, he was somewhat concerned about being quarantined at home.

On the afternoon of the 22nd, a video of an ambulance towing away an elderly man and a heavily armed doctor was released by the community's owners. At that moment, I thought: WE SHOULD GO! If we don't get out of here, we're never GONNA GET OUT OF HERE!

At 2:00 on the morning of the 23rd, news of the city closing came out. In the morning, we hurry to clean up. I thought: CAN GO, cleaning up before the trip is consistent with my usual habits; can not go, come home or clean. I did these preparations with a sense of desertion until I set out.

Sitting in the car, looking at this familiar city, I thought: I really want to escape? The fat man stressed that he could not open the window without his permission. I thought: How sick is this? The windows don't open, the air in this city doesn't breathe freely? A little sadness passed through my heart.

The traffic on the 27 bridge was as usual. In order to calm down, I asked the fat man: Are they all going out of town? He said, of course. That way, I feel a little less guilty. However, the remorse did not last long. Soon, to the high-speed toll station out of Wuhan. This place is crawling with cops. All cars turn around and head back downtown. At that moment, there is a loss, but more is down-to-earth, I freed from self-blame.

When we got home, we all went to bed. The fat man began to go in and out, inventorying supplies, and going down to the supermarket to do some shopping; at night he took out our luggage one by one in silence. His main battleground was the kitchen, where he kept muttering about how this year's New Year had been rushed and how few dishes there were. But I think, husband and wife relationship harmonious, parent-child relationship, like every day in the new year, do not care how many dishes.

I have always been grateful for the experiences I have had in my life. On the first day of the siege, from remorse to disappointment to stability, I believed it would broaden my life.

We have a study group, we do family therapy together, and we throw our weight around together. On the day of the siege, my flight disturbed the snow, and she was usually a confident and radiant woman, but also vulnerable -- a daughter, as it were. The daughter needs to take medicine because of illness, she is very worried after the closure of the city, travel difficulties, can not buy medicine. When she saw me leave, she wanted to leave. That day, the crowd was filled with anxiety, fear, agitation. L Snow said: If not die, we summer get together! L Rong later said: At that time, I felt scared and sad, and I didn't know if I would see you again for the rest of my life, but I felt less sad when I was most scared to be with you. And W Fang, as a doctor, expressed her determination to stay in Wuhan, which helped us to smooth the last creases of panic and panic, and became our tranquilizer.

On the day of the city's traffic ban, we each gave her a small red envelope for her birthday. She said she would use the money to buy everyone a big meal when we met again in the summer. She was anxious that day, too, and the restrictions might have affected her ability to buy medicine for her daughter. The next day, she told us that in her condition she could go out and buy medicine. She left the house in a raincoat, double mask and gloves.

After the closure of the city, people's life from the original a large social circle directly into the existence of only family members of the small circle, many usually not easily aware of the significance of re-emerged.

I used to worry about fat people not coming home on time, but not anymore. So far he's only gone out for two things: to Buy Supplies; to throw out the garbage. And never to be seen again. Come to think of it, it saved him a phone bill and a lot less resentment for coming home late. Before at home, to him to do something is a little bit uneasy, afraid he was tired and unwilling to do, now tell him to do things with complete peace of mind. Through this incident, I will not give fat people "always at the bottom of Maslow's hierarchy of needs, " the label. This particular time, when you re-examine your relationship, you may find a bright spot that you haven't noticed for years.

After the city was sealed, time took on a new meaning. There was plenty of time, lots of things to do: catch up on TV shows, read the books in the bookcase, brush up on some consulting reports... plenty of time, but the planning criteria were different: it used to be the exact time to do something, now it's: 2-3 hours after you get up is study time, which may be 10 am or 2 pm, which is an accurate and inaccurate free time.

Since the city was shut down, I've reorganized the routines of my two children. No matter what time the eldest son gets up in the morning, the first thing must be to study; after lunch is responsible for washing the dishes; make time to play games with his younger brother.

I told him, let's not make a particular period of time special. We can still do what we used to do, such as learning, such as self-discipline... even if we are in this situation, it is far from the end of the world. It is the duty of every one of US ordinary people to study and live earnestly.

Starting from the second day of "closing the city" , our family started the activity of Reading Club, which had been stopped for two years. Dad, who almost never reads, was the best at book parties, took the most careful notes, the oldest son was the most knowledgeable about reading, and I was the worst organizer. At last they all felt cheated, so you called us to read in the name of a book club!

In addition, everyone in the family began to exercise. The hibernating treadmill comes in handy, with everyone running for half an hour a day. We chased each other around the house, constantly changing sides, sometimes as Ultraman, sometimes as a nameless villain, with our little brother calling the shots.

After the city was shut down, we were more hygienic than ever. People wash their hands many times a day. There was a time when the younger son wouldn't wash his face, but now there's no such thing. When he sees US coughing once in a while, he says to the other two, get away from him, he's coughing! You see, this 3-year-old's cognition has been updated by this epidemic.

The younger son, at an even younger age, called the cough the purple disease, a term he coined himself. Today, we haven't been out of the House for nearly 10 days. Once he finished collecting his toys and asked me, can we go out now?
Me: Do you mean go out?
He: HMM.
Me: We can't go out yet
He tilted his head very serious look at me: Why?
Me: Because now a lot of people in Wuhan are sick, we go out will be very dangerous, will be infected.
He: What's wrong with them? Is it purple?
Me: Well, it's purple.
He: We don't get Purple Disease at home!
Me: Well, yeah, we don't get purple disease when we stay home.
He: The People in Wuhan are sick, so let the doctor come to save us.
Me: Yes, many, many doctors came to save Wuhan.

This reminds me of the day I left Wuhan on the 23rd. I asked him to wear a mask when I walked out of my room. I did not know how to persuade him, but in spite of his cries I held him in one hand and pressed the broken side of his face with the other. I think he was so resistant to wearing the mask because the adult panic had spread to the children.

It is this 3-year-old child, in our Wuhan people open the window, standing in the balcony, "Wuhan refueling" , he repeatedly waved his small fist: Wuhan Refueling, Wuhan Refueling! His childish voice in the Dark Silent Wuhan Winter Night, it seems so sonorous and powerful, and I, only shouted out the first sentence "Wuhan refueling, " and no longer cry. I looked at my young child with tears streaming down my face. Son, do you know what we are going through! As a part of Wuhan, I am proud of you, you help your mother, also help our family, but also help us all Wuhan, shout out our heart most painful the most heartfelt voice, Foshan Wuhan Go!

So far, the mood of our family has remained optimistic, free, calm this tone, but also always hidden some helpless and sad, and can not go out of depression.

On New Year's Day, the fat man made several dishes, watching the two children eat with relish, think do not know how long to take them out to play, both happy and sad. On this day, we had an extra meal of rice than usual. The fat person reminds me repeatedly, do not send the vegetable friend circle, the vegetable is too few, is ashamed.

This dinner, under normal circumstances should be called New Year's Eve dinner. The fat man had a few drinks, the younger one was sleeping, the older one was watching TV, and the two of us were chatting over drinks, like we'd just gotten married before graduation. Back then, we used to have a little dinner, a little wine, in our little house in the doctor's building. Suddenly, more than 10 years have passed, there are two more children. Over the years, I do not know how many quarrels, marriage do not know how many times in the heart divorced.

We all contributed to our little family, and we all did. But it doesn't matter. In 2020, we're still stuck together.

On the third night after the "closing of the city" , a video emerged from the circle of friends. A Wuhan man shouted across the Balcony in Wuhan dialect: "opposite, open the window a quarrel, to crazy, there is no one oh. " I looked and laughed and cried, looked again and again, in that moment, I know, I first fell in love with Wuhan, the city I've lived in for over 20 years. If you are not Wuhan people, if you have not been "closed city" , you may not be like me, so understanding of the call to the full of Wuhan People's unique strong, optimistic, moved and sad.

That shouting, I feel is lonely and not lonely, is sad, is happy, is strong, mixed feelings. I feel like I'm living in a city that's so loving, a city that has hope. A friend said: through this epidemic, I believe we will love this city more, whether it is left or fled, this is the collective unconscious.

These days, the refrigerator freezer snack cabinet looked empty, the younger son no longer willing to eat only two meals a day, often to snack cabinet there run. The fat man is becoming more and more difficult as a cook. Every day there is only one dish at noon and a meal of noodles at night. He wants to go shopping all the time. That day, I finally got some food on the Internet. The fat man went downstairs to get it himself, and bought some snacks for his beloved son at the same time.

We dare not go out more and more, the community notified the community of suspected and confirmed infection number, is a hard-hit area. Pessimistic when I will feel that the danger seems to be getting closer and closer to us, so close that I dare not open the balcony window, dare not in the balcony drying clothes. The distance between upstairs and downstairs seems further.

The experience of Fengcheng may be understood as a kind of suffering experience. As the ordeal begins, a new set of human interaction scenarios unfolds simultaneously. Wechat many people sent greetings, most of them out of sincere concern, do not rule out that some people are just curious. I'm trying to get a sense of authenticity.

There are a lot of mental institutions doing crisis intervention, a friend told me. This is an opportunity. I can not respond to the word "opportunity. ". At this point, it's hard for all of us to keep our anxieties in check, let alone help others? I'm not sure I'm capable of supporting people in need.

At this point, I thought of the word "AWE. ". We need to learn to be in awe of the thoughts and attitudes of others, rather than to judge them directly. In the face of an epidemic, whether it is a medical staff or patients, ordinary citizens, each person's psychological pressure is different, how effective the temperature to help them, is I understand the awe in this epidemic.

The fear of this epidemic also includes the fear of life, the fear of not going out, the fear of wearing a mask if you have to go out, and the fear of truth, the fear of not listening to rumors and spreading them. Above, as an ordinary Wuhan residents, a psychological consultant, in the city during this period of real experience, there are flat and calm, but also some panic and fear.

On New Year's Day, the fat man made several dishes, watching the two children eat with relish, think do not know how long to take them out to play, both happy and sad. On this day, we had an extra meal of rice than usual. The fat person reminds me repeatedly, do not send the vegetable friend circle, the vegetable is too few, is ashamed.

This dinner, under normal circumstances should be called New Year's Eve dinner. The fat man had a few drinks, the younger one was sleeping, the older one was watching TV, and the two of us were chatting over drinks, like we'd just gotten married before graduation. Back then, we used to have a little dinner, a little wine, in our little house in the doctor's building. Suddenly, more than 10 years have passed, there are two more children. Over the years, I do not know how many quarrels, marriage do not know how many times in the heart divorced.

We all contributed to our little family, and we all did. But it doesn't matter. In 2020, we're still stuck together.

On the third night after the "closing of the city" , a video emerged from the circle of friends. A Wuhan man shouted across the Balcony in Wuhan dialect: "opposite, open the window a quarrel, to crazy, there is no one oh. " I looked and laughed and cried, looked again and again, in that moment, I know, I first fell in love with Wuhan, the city I've lived in for over 20 years. If you are not Wuhan people, if you have not been "closed city" , you may not be like me, so understanding of the call to the full of Wuhan People's unique strong, optimistic, moved and sad.

That shouting, I feel is lonely and not lonely, is sad, is happy, is strong, mixed feelings. I feel like I'm living in a city that's so loving, a city that has hope. A friend said: through this epidemic, I believe we will love this city more, whether it is left or fled, this is the collective unconscious.

These days, the refrigerator freezer snack cabinet looked empty, the younger son no longer willing to eat only two meals a day, often to snack cabinet there run. The fat man is becoming more and more difficult as a cook. Every day there is only one dish at noon and a meal of noodles at night. He wants to go shopping all the time. That day, I finally got some food on the Internet. The fat man went downstairs to get it himself, and bought some snacks for his beloved son at the same time.

We dare not go out more and more, the community notified the community of suspected and confirmed infection number, is a hard-hit area. Pessimistic when I will feel that the danger seems to be getting closer and closer to us, so close that I dare not open the balcony window, dare not in the balcony drying clothes. The distance between upstairs and downstairs seems further.

The experience of Fengcheng may be understood as a kind of suffering experience. As the ordeal begins, a new set of human interaction scenarios unfolds simultaneously. Wechat many people sent greetings, most of them out of sincere concern, do not rule out that some people are just curious. I'm trying to get a sense of authenticity.

There are a lot of mental institutions doing crisis intervention, a friend told me. This is an opportunity. I can not respond to the word "opportunity. ". At this point, it's hard for all of us to keep our anxieties in check, let alone help others? I'm not sure I'm capable of supporting people in need.

At this point, I thought of the word "AWE. ". We need to learn to be in awe of the thoughts and attitudes of others, rather than to judge them directly. In the face of an epidemic, whether it is a medical staff or patients, ordinary citizens, each person's psychological pressure is different, how effective the temperature to help them, is I understand the awe in this epidemic.

The fear of this epidemic also includes the fear of life, the fear of not going out, the fear of wearing a mask if you have to go out, and the fear of truth, the fear of not listening to rumors and spreading them. Above, as an ordinary Wuhan residents, a psychological consultant, in the city during this period of real experience, there are flat and calm, but also some panic and fear.
